        "4b65e73d-1857-488c-adaf-275450955184"
      ],
      "dct:title": {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "COVID-19 HPSC HIU Timeseries Local Electoral Area Mapped"
      },
      "dct:description": {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "<p>Dataset of the 14-Day Incidence rate per 100,000 population of confirmed COVID-19 cases by Local Electoral Area (LEA).  This data includes confirmed cases (PCR) only and does not include positive antigen results uploaded to the HSE portal.  In total, there are 166 LEA’s across Ireland.</p><p>Please note: For confidentiality reasons, following consultation with the CSO, all LEA's with values below 5 have been suppressed to 'Less than 5'. Where a rate per 100k is set to 'Less than 5' it means that the LEA has a 14-Day incidence below 5 and its value has been suppressed to show 'Less than 5'. This is not an indication of zero (0) confirmed cases.</p><p>For a proportion of notified COVID-19 cases, their location on the map may reflect their place of work rather than their home address. Confirmed cases have been geo-coded and allocated to LEA's by the Health Intelligence Unit (HIU) at the HSE.</p><p>Time series dataset from August 2020 to May 2022.</p><p>** Due to the surge of cases over the Christmas period 2021, and increased processing times, there is a gap in the historic LEA time series for cases created between 21st December 2021 and 21st January 2022. **  </p>"
      },
